\displaystyle \frac{AF+FC}{FC} = \frac{AG+GC}{GC} \implies \frac{AC}{FC} = \frac{AC}{GC} \implies FC = GC
\frac {AE}{EB} = \frac{AF}{FC}\quad\quad (1)
\frac{AE}{EB} = \frac{AG}{GC}\quad\quad (2)
\frac{AF}{FC} = \frac{AG}{GC}\quad\quad (3)
 \frac {AF}{FC} + \frac{FC}{FC} = \frac {AG}{GC} + \frac{GC}{GC}
